race.description: Glenroy Chaff - A.j. Scahill Cup Handicap (L)
race.comment: CAPTAIN PLUTO (2) was far too good in the Luckygray Stakes last start, reeling in his rivals to win comfortably on the line as the fave. This shapes similarly, and the rise in trip won't be an issue. Will need some luck in the run, but expecting him to bring up back-to-back wins if he can improve on his latest effort. OPPORTUNISTIC (9) has been disappointing this campaign, though getting back onto the bigger track at Ascot and out in trip can see him recapture his best form. Not willing to go against him just yet. FILTHY HABITS (6) led the field up in the Luckgray and stuck on well enough first-up from a spell. Suspect he'll be better for that run there and he is likely to be up front once again from the draw. Will take plenty of catching if he gets it all his own way. MEMORY PARADE (8) closed off well over 1800m last start and rises to this trip for the first time. Won't be far away. BUCKETS RIDGE (1) can improve now out in trip and from a better gate.
